Larran's key is a key obtained from killing monsters while on a Slayer task given by Krystilia. It is used to open Larran’s small and big chests.

The exact odds of receiving a key scales with the monster's Combat level. For levels 1-80, the probability follows a curve between 1/1972 at level 1 to 1/100 at level 80[1]. For levels 81 or higher, the odds are between 1/99 and 1/50, scaling linearly and capping at level 350[2], as reflected in the equation below. In addition, if players are assigned to kill slayer monsters, the drop chance is increased by 25%,[3] and any monsters killed within the Wilderness Slayer Cave have a further 15% increased chance to drop a key.[4]

The probability P {\displaystyle P} of obtaining a key when killing a monster with combat level L {\displaystyle L} is given by P = { 1 ⌊ 3 10 × ( 80 − L ) 2 ⌋ + 100 if  L ∈ ( 0 , 80 ] 1 ⌊ − 5 27 × L ⌋ + 115 if  L ∈ ( 80 , 350 ] {\displaystyle P={\begin{cases}{\frac {1}{\left\lfloor {\frac {3}{10}}\times (80-L)^{2}\right\rfloor +100}}&{\text{if }}L\in (0,80]\\{\frac {1}{\left\lfloor -{\frac {5}{27}}\times L\right\rfloor +115}}&{\text{if }}L\in (80,350]\end{cases}}} .

While untradeable, the killer will be able to receive the key upon killing their opponent. If the killer is an Ironman, the key will be automatically destroyed.

'''Larran's key''' is a key obtained from killing monsters while on a [[Slayer task]] given by [[Krystilia]]. It is used to open [[Larran]]’s [[Larran's small chest|small]] and [[Larran's big chest|big chests]].

The exact odds of receiving a key scales with the monster's [[Combat level]]. For levels 1-80, the probability follows a curve between 1/1972 at level 1 to 1/100 at level 80{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1152237123778555904|date=19 July 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/lPWEG|archivedate=19 July 2019|quote=NPC combat levels 1-80: 1 in (100 + floor((3 / 10) x (80 - level) x (80 - level))).}}. For levels 81 or higher, the odds are between 1/99 and 1/50, scaling linearly and capping at level 350{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1152237123778555904|date=19 July 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/lPWEG|archivedate=19 July 2019|quote=NPC combat levels 81-350+: 1 in (50 + number scaled linearly between 99 at level 81 and 50 at level 350)}}, as reflected in the equation below. In addition, if players are assigned to kill [[slayer monster]]s, the drop chance is increased by 25%,{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1152237123778555904|date=19 July 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/lPWEG|archivedate=19 July 2019|quote=If the NPC's Slayer req >= 2, multiply chance by 25%.}} and any monsters killed within the [[Wilderness Slayer Cave]] have a further 15% increased chance to drop a key.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1326275335969796096|date=11 November 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/dtbEO|archivedate=10 November 2020|quote=15%}}

The probability <math>P</math> of obtaining a key when killing a monster with combat level <math>L</math> is given by 
<math>P = \begin{cases} \frac{1}{\left \lfloor \frac{3}{10} \times (80 - L)^2 \right\rfloor + 100} &\text{if } L\in (0,80] \\  \frac{1}{\left \lfloor-\frac{5}{27} \times L \right\rfloor + 115} &\text{if } L \in (80, 350]\end{cases}</math>.

While untradeable, the killer will be able to receive the key upon killing their opponent. If the killer is an [[Ironman Mode|Ironman]], the key will be automatically destroyed.
